   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><w>ce</w><w>sūtär</w><w>śīlabhādre</w><w>y<supplied>āt</supplied>k<supplied>a</supplied></w><w><supplied>paiykatsi</supplied></w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">this sūtra Śīlabhadra has ordered (to be written)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">This probably completes <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkns17and900"/> (<bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault2007"/><citedRange>208</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note type="remarks">The Sanskrit text has been omitted from the transcription/transliteration.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">The top of the akṣara <hi>bh[ā]</hi> is covered by a piece that is flipped over from the recto. The reading is nevertheless certain. The traces of the last akṣara are compatible with <hi>tsi</hi> (for <hi>si</hi> they would be too low).</note></p>
         </div>
